cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image and video segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of an end-to-end encoder-decoder style 3D CNN also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed 3D separable convolution technique may also indicate that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the extension of the framework to video action segmentation suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of a classifier to predict action labels may also suggest that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
